[{"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-20T17:19:05+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Illustration of location plackets dropped on a map.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/8G2ulN5PGbVd7ab-6LgGYQJo7Ww=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73736974/STK476_LOCATION_DATA_CVIRGINIA_B.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Cath Virginia / The Verge, Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"so6Lnn\">SafeRent, an AI screening tool used by landlords, will no longer use AI-powered \u201cscores\u201d to evaluate whether someone using housing vouchers would make a good tenant. On Wednesday, US District Judge Angel Kelley <a href=\"https://www.documentcloud.org/documents/25355973-saferent-final-approval-order-11-20-2024?responsive=1&amp;title=1\">issued final approval</a> for a roughly $2.3 million settlement to prevent SafeRent from discriminating against tenants based on income and race.</p>\n<p id=\"5LC7CA\">The <a href=\"https://www.cohenmilstein.com/case-study/louis-et-al-v-saferent-solutions-et-al/\">settlement stems fro", "id": 1554569, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/20/24297692/ai-landlord-tool-saferent-low-income-tenants-discrimination-settlement", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "AI landlord screening tool will stop scoring low-income tenants after discrimination suit", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-20T16:54:36+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"A conceptual rendering of Blue Origin\u2019s cargo lander\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/epYvSSXtXDGp1DF-Ze7W44FMPB8=/273x0:2139x1244/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73736882/nasa_blue_origin_lander.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption><em>A conceptual rendering of Blue Origin\u2019s cargo lander.</em> | Image: Blue Origin / NASA</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"Bl6KXh\">After <a href=\"https://www.nasa.gov/directorates/esdmd/artemis-campaign-development-division/human-landing-system-program/work-underway-on-large-cargo-landers-for-nasas-artemis-moon-missions/\">asking both SpaceX and Blue Origin to develop cargo landers</a> for its Artemis missions, NASA has <a href=\"https://www.nasa.gov/news-release/nasa-plans-to-assign-missions-for-two-future-artemis-cargo-landers/\">announced plans</a><strong> </strong>to use those landers to deliver heavy equipment to the Moon. </p>\n<p id=\"eoNceh\">The agency wants Elon Musk\u2019s SpaceX to use its Starship ", "id": 1554570, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/20/24301744/nasa-spacex-blue-origin-cargo-mission-artemis", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "NASA wants SpaceX and Blue Origin to deliver cargo to the moon", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-20T16:01:20+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Illustration of Microsoft\u2019s Windows logo\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/4wmOhAIhft29ZfB9bbkxoPRvY5c=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73736771/acastro_STK109_microsoft_02.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration by Alex Castro / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"847U2p\">Microsoft has been trying to convince Windows 10 users to upgrade to Windows 11 for months now, ahead of the end of support date for Windows 10 in October, 2025. Earlier this year, Microsoft <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/4/11/24127497/microsoft-windows-10-upgrade-prompt-windows-11\">started using fullscreen prompts</a> to warn Windows 10 users about the support cutoff, and now it\u2019s using similar prompts to try and tempt people to buy a new Windows 11 PC instead.</p>\n<p id=\"11vD2J\">Over the weekend <a href=\"https://x.com/femceIs/status/1858314837845229737\">some</a> Windows 10 <a href=\"https://x.com/JustinWhang/status/1859033", "id": 1554234, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/20/24301768/microsoft-windows-10-upgrade-prompt-copilot-plus-pcs", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Microsoft tries to convince Windows 10 users to buy a new PC with full-screen prompts", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-20T15:46:29+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Two smartphone screenshots of the Messenger video calling feature. Left: the person making the call; right: call settings screen.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/duvbe2PMvv99bi6i7x1wwABQd6s=/66x0:1848x1188/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73736729/02_HD_Video_Calls_Carousel_01_2.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Meta</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"WhMeeo\">Meta has <a href=\"https://about.fb.com/news/2024/11/introducing-ai-backgrounds-noise-suppression-and-more-messenger-calling/\">announced</a> that it\u2019s adding HD video calling and noise suppression to its Messenger app, along with several other features like AI backgrounds that help bring it up to par with other popular smartphone video calling apps. </p>\n<p id=\"bdjjrN\">HD video calling is enabled by default on Wi-Fi but can be turned on for calls using your cell data plan in the \u201cCall settings\u201d menu. You\u2019ll also find options to adjust noise cancellation or switch your", "id": 1553890, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/20/24301722/meta-facebook-messenger-hd-video-noise-suppression-video-calls-ai-backgrounds", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Messenger video calls will look and sound better \u2014 and add AI backgrounds", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-20T15:18:12+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Vector illustration of the Sonos logo.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/mF03LfQWcLWhKl9yg7XzPgilEfY=/0x1:4250x2834/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73736646/_STK084_SONOS_A.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Cath Virginia / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"5ns28c\">After its foray into headphones, the next major new product category from Sonos is rumored to be a video streaming box similar to a Roku, Amazon Fire TV, or Apple TV. Such a device has been rumored for ages now, with <a href=\"https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2023-11-21/sonos-plans-400-500-headphones-tv-set-top-box-video-roam-2-new-sound-bar\"><em>Bloomberg</em></a> previously reporting that its price is expected to fall between $150 and $200. And today we got confirmation (or at least something close to it) that the Sonos streamer will run an operating system built by The Trade Desk, a digital advertising business. </p>\n<p id=\"GhuczW\"><a href=\"ht", "id": 1553891, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/20/24301519/sonos-trade-desk-venture-tv-operating-system", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Sonos\u2019 smart TV plans might have found an OS", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-20T14:04:10+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"T-Mobile logo with illustrated background.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/DR5A1s_dyk6ckELzdEW2LKKVip0=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73736486/acastro_STK067__01.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Good one, T-Mo.</em> | Illustration by Alex Castro / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"MUSNt5\">T-Mobile isn\u2019t exactly known for having <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/1/20/23563825/tmobile-data-breach-api-customer-accounts-hacker-security\">a stellar track record against hackers</a>, but it seems that the company actually caught a recent cyberattack in progress and shut it down in time. <a href=\"https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-11-19/t-mobile-said-to-have-caught-hackers-early-averting-data-leak\"><em>Bloomberg</em> reports</a> that T-Mobile detected suspicious activity in a recent attempt to access customer data and kicked the cyber criminals out before they were able to infiltrate deeper", "id": 1553450, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/20/24301570/t-mobile-network-breach-stopped-salt-typhoon", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "T-Mobile actually stopped some hackers from stealing customer data", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-20T13:45:46+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"A screenshot of today\u2019s NYT Connections on the alternate puzzle creator.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/sVo5GJF0k8cdhwVlfMUUReQwl4k=/25x0:2008x1322/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73736412/Screenshot_2024_11_20_at_10.41.57_AM.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption><em>A screenshot of today\u2019s NYT Connections on the </em><a class=\"ql-link\" href=\"https://connections.swellgarfo.com/nyt/528\" target=\"_blank\"><em>alternate puzzle creator</em></a><em>.</em> | Screenshot by Jay Peters / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"xix8R3\"><em>The New York Times</em> wants to shut down a copy of its popular <em>Connections</em> word game. The publication sent a cease and desist letter to the owner of <a href=\"https://connections.swellgarfo.com\">a website</a> that lets you make your own <em>Connections</em> games. The site also has a full archive of all of the <em>NYT\u2019s</em> past <em>Connections</em> puzzles, which the <em>NYT</em> keeps behi", "id": 1553451, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/20/24301557/new-york-times-connections-creator-take-down", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The New York Times is trying to shut down a popular Connections puzzle creator", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-20T12:46:04+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Screenshot from FFXIV Mobile featuring a party of characters fighting against Titan, a large monster with the power over earth.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/RD8xrjkXp3HMHr_EToddJFxT76I=/300x0:3540x2160/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73736292/ed3da3fc_b819_45c5_a7d9_557f0a69cae2.0.jpeg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Square Enix / Lightspeed Studios</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"AlnEOw\">Have you heard that the <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2022/1/11/22877031/final-fantasy-xiv-endwalker-review-square-enix-pc\">critically acclaimed MMORPG <em>Final Fantasy XIV</em></a> is getting a mobile version? In a video announcement, <em>Final Fantasy XIV</em> game director Naoki Yoshida announced <em>FFXIV Mobile</em>, a joint production between Square Enix and Tencent\u2019s Lightspeed Studios<em>. </em>The announcement was accompanied by a teaser trailer showing Warriors of Light in locations all across the game\u2019s world of Eorzea", "id": 1553012, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/20/24301435/final-fantasy-14-mobile-square-enix", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Final Fantasy XIV Mobile will bring Eorzea to your phone", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-20T12:31:00+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"An image showing the Threads logo\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/TXVRSh_PTgt8ixoR_mZxOwTJmkY=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73736258/STK156_Instagram_threads_1.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration: The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"GKcY4p\">Just five days after Meta started testing custom feeds in Threads, the company is already <a href=\"https://www.threads.net/@threads/post/DCmWZGGO229?xmt=AQGzpwRLdz_RW4IemEKLKx66KW-2bfzMri5WyhjruyVOgg\">rolling them out to everyone</a>. With custom feeds, you can track topics and accounts in one feed, making it easier to keep an eye on specific things that matter to you.</p>\n<p id=\"N0WZAN\">To make a custom feed, search for a topic, then click on the three dots menu next to the search bar, and then click on the \u201cCreate new feed\u201d option. Custom feeds can also contain information about multiple topics \u2014 just add a new one from a search or, on desktop, from the", "id": 1552540, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/20/24301587/threads-custom-feeds-rolling-out", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Threads\u2019 custom feeds are already rolling out", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-20T12:14:02+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"The Google Drive logo on a background of geometric shapes in various shades of blue.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/6ZR-kxdijpf3mDs5UKDvcV0R0Jc=/0x0:3000x2000/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73736212/acastro_STK459_03.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration by Alex Castro / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"5ALlFY\">Google has released a beta version of the Google Drive desktop app that supports Windows 11 running on Snapdragon chips. The app offers the same features as on computers with Intel and AMD chips, with the exception of the Outlook Meet plugin, a <a href=\"https://support.google.com/drive/thread/308624582/drive-for-desktop-arm64-support\">Google employee wrote</a> in a Drive community forum post <a href=\"https://www.androidauthority.com/google-drive-desktop-windows-arm-release-3501392/\">spotted by <em>Android Authority</em></a><em>. </em></p>\n<p id=\"WC6h1t\">You can download the beta from Google <a href", "id": 1552541, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/20/24301546/google-drive-desktop-app-beta-available-windows-snapdragon-arm-pc", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Google\u2019s Drive app is now available for Windows on Arm", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-20T12:12:06+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Vector illustration of the Xbox logo.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/cc0FP11ZirldQQvfl2SikXfGbSU=/20x0:2021x1334/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73736206/STK048_XBOX_C.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"PM6V7U\">Microsoft is starting to open up Xbox Cloud Gaming to <a href=\"https://support.xbox.com/en-US/help/games-apps/cloud-gaming/set-up-smart-tv-xbox-app\">existing Xbox game libraries</a> today. Xbox Game Pass Ultimate subscribers can now stream 50 games that they already own, including <em>Balatro</em>, <em>Baldur\u2019s Gate 3</em>, a variety of <em>Final Fantasy</em> titles, and <em>Hogwarts Legacy</em>.</p>\n<p id=\"ElV7O1\">The expansion to 50 more games is just the beginning of opening up the Xbox game library to cloud streaming. \u201cOur library of cloud-playable titles will continue to grow, as we work with our partners around the world to bring you a diverse and expansive select", "id": 1552542, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/20/24300547/xbox-cloud-gaming-game-library-streaming", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Xbox cloud streaming expands beyond Game Pass to games you own", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-20T11:54:48+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Ford Cologne - Electric car Explorer\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/IMChrBMrzNEAOAB06Km2afXAnE4=/0x0:6425x4283/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73736139/2185099372.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo by Rolf Vennenbernd/picture alliance via Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"Ne9ovk\">Ford said it would cut 4,000 jobs from its business in Europe, while also lowering production estimates for its upcoming <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/3/26/24112744/ford-explorer-ev-all-electric-range-europe\">Explorer</a> and <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/10/24195756/ford-capri-ev-crossover-announce-europe\">Capri</a> electric vehicles. </p>\n<p id=\"uUpQSH\"><a href=\"https://s201.q4cdn.com/693218008/files/doc_news/2024/Nov/20/Ford-Europe-Press-Release-Nov-20-2024.pdf\">The planned cuts</a>, which amount to 14 percent of the automaker\u2019s European operations, will primarily affect its workers in Germany and the UK, with", "id": 1552543, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/20/24301507/ford-retracts-in-europe-with-layoffs-and-lower-ev-production", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Ford retracts in Europe with layoffs and lower EV production ", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-20T11:49:47+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"A closeup of Garmin\u2019s Venu Sq 2 display.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/XWOQHu1fxYrNw2xs7k0GJuKgRNE=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73736131/226428_Garmin_Venu_Sq_2_AKrales_0017.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Garmin\u2019s Venu Sq 2 comes with an impressive set of health features, including hydration tracking, which its Fitbit rivals lack.</em> | Image: Amelia Holowaty Krales / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"LIZStc\">If you\u2019re looking to upgrade your old Fitbit, <strong>Garmin\u2019s Venu Sq 2</strong> smartwatch<strong> </strong>is <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/23691498/best-garmin-smartwatch-fitness-tracker-wearables\">a stylish alternative</a> that\u2019s currently down to an all-time low price. Normally $249.99, right now you can buy the wearable for $149.99 ($100 off) at <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0B5VVNJBF/?tag=theverge02-20\" rel=\"sponsored nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Amazon</a>, <a", "id": 1552544, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/20/24301486/garmin-venu-sq-2-deal-sale", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Garmin\u2019s Venu Sq 2, our favorite Fitbit alternative, hits its lowest price ever", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-20T11:20:05+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/DVf1bbNUhWhdE_nAhy-VDizogIg=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73736045/092524_MagSafe_Qi2_BG_ADiBenedetto_0019.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Most MagSafe power bank kickstands are too flimsy to safely hold an iPhone. Anker\u2019s design is much better.</em> | Photo by Antonio G. Di Benedetto / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"0dOaLs\">We\u2019ll soon see an explosion of <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24293826/best-early-black-friday-deals-2024-amazon-walmart-buy-target-tech-sale\">early Black Friday deals</a>, with several extended sales kicking off tomorrow and more underway as the week itself approaches. That said, there are still many bargains to be had right now.</p>\n<div class=\"c-float-left c-float-hang\"><aside id=\"d10BMi\"><div data-anthem-component=\"readmore\" data-anthem-component-data='{\"stories\":[{\"title\":\"The Verge\u2019s guide to Black Friday 2024 \",\"url\":\"https://ww", "id": 1552001, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/20/24301443/ankers-6-6k-maggo-power-bank-black-friday-deal-sale", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Anker\u2019s excellent 6.6K MagGo Power Bank is down to an absolute steal at $19.99", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-20T10:44:51+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"An image showing the Echo Show 21\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/ZL44nMFfG7J1Al1j89G2KXfqHv8=/0x200:1200x1000/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73735924/amazon_echo_show_21.0.jpeg\" />\n        <figcaption>Now that\u2019s a big smart display. | Image: Amazon</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"RJbN4q\">Amazon\u2019s first wall-mounted smart display just got a big upgrade. Today, <a href=\"https://www.aboutamazon.com/news/devices/echo-show-21-amazon-smart-tv\">the company announced</a> the launch of <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0CDWWS127?tag=theverge02-20\" rel=\"sponsored nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">the Echo Show 21</a>, an upgrade to the <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/22839220/amazon-echo-show-15-review-wall-mounted-alexa-tablet-kitchen-tv\">Echo Show 15</a> that debuted in 2022. The new model has a 21-inch screen with 1080p resolution for $399.99. Amazon says it has better audio quality than the original Show 15 and nearly d", "id": 1552002, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/20/24301489/amazon-echo-show-21-smart-display-price-specs-release-date", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Amazon\u2019s new\u00a0Echo\u00a0Show 21 has a huge screen and built-in\u00a0smart home\u00a0hub  ", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-20T10:42:48+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Illustration of the Chrome logo on a bright and dark red background.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/8gAOsoSkKGK08IJP_uGy61kcRC0=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73735918/STK114_Google_Chrome_01.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"r6yQOi\">The latest version of Chrome (Version 131.0.6778.86) has addressed an issue in the browser that broke the ability to highlight text on some websites over the weekend, Google\u2019s Scott Westover confirmed to <em>The Verge </em>in an email. </p>\n<p id=\"3gbVgD\">We tested the change, and found that we were able to highlight text within stories on sites like <em>Bloomberg</em> and <em>The Verge</em>, and in the post composer on X, both in updated Windows and Mac versions of Chrome. It\u2019s not clear whether the change applies to other Chromium-based browsers, such as Arc, which continues to be affected in our testing.</p>\n<p id=\"dgp0Dm\">West", "id": 1552003, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/20/24301471/google-chrome-text-highlighting-visible-issue-fixed", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Google fixes Chrome issue that broke text highlighting on some sites", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-20T10:24:39+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"A render of the DS Pixel Keyboard floating over a reflective lake.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/YujT1KXOQ2OpkHKj0dEG2Cyr1R0=/0x0:1177x785/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73735840/ds_pixel_keyboard1.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>The DS Pixel Keyboard combines the flexibility of a touchscreen keyboard with the tactile feedback of a physical one.</em> | Image: DS</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"tLMrEC\">The creators of the <a href=\"https://www.ds-keyboard.com/\">DS Pixel Keyboard</a> have come up with a potential solution to the challenge of typing on a touchscreen. The keyboard, which doubles as a display, includes a removable \u201celectrostatic capacitive keycap\u201d frame that sits atop its touchscreen, providing physical keys that facilitate touch typing.</p>\n<p id=\"n98Xv7\">The DS Pixel Keyboard is now <a href=\"https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/1649756249/ds-pixel-keyboardbreaking-the-monotony-of-keyboards\">available th", "id": 1551500, "langu