index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Stellantis\u2019 electric STLA Frame gives vehicles 690 miles of range with an extender", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-20T10:09:40+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"A screenshot from the Lapz app\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/xdVRVvkHILg1dDogxdb5xUe0Yq4=/141x0:2256x1410/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73735812/lapz_app_1.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Lapz</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"CusILR\">Lapz, the Apple Vision Pro app that puts Formula One races in mixed reality, is on hold after F1 asked it to stop using its content, <a href=\"https://www.uploadvr.com/f1-lapz-forced-to-stop-apple-vision-pro-testflight/\">as reported by <em>UploadVR</em></a><em>. </em>In a message posted to its <a href=\"https://discord.gg/AAeF5fq6um\">Discord channel</a>, Lapz says it halted distribution through TestFlight while it explores \u201clicensing opportunities with various racing leagues and tech partners.\u201d</p>\n<p id=\"2UILmD\">\u201cF1\u00ae have respectfully asked us to discontinue the use of their F1\u00aeTV broadcast rights in our platform for the time being while we continue to advance our roadmap and enhance ", "id": 1551502, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/20/24301420/apple-vision-pro-viral-lapz-app-f1-complaint", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Vision Pro\u2019s viral Lapz app put on hold after F1 complaint", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-20T09:12:20+00:00", "description": "  \n\n  